// TO SEPERATE ALL WORDS OR SEPARATED CHARACTER AND PRINT IT ON DIFF LINES BUT NOT SPECIAL CHARACTERS , TRIM BEFORE STARTING TO PRINT IT ON DIFFERENT LINES AND PRINT THE TOTAL NUMBER BEFORE PRINTING EACH ONE OF THEM
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = scan.nextLine();
        
        // Write your code here.
        s=s.trim();
        if(s.length()==0)
        {
            System.out.println(0); scan.close();
            return ;
        }
        String[] tokens = s.split("[^A-Za-z]+");
        System.out.println(tokens.length);
        for(String token:tokens)
            System.out.println(token);
        
        
        scan.close();
            
    }
}
